---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About SpeakForWater"
  description="The story, methodology, and AI ethics behind SpeakForWater — the daily AI-narrated water research podcast by Ehsan Kahrizi."
>
  <article class="about">
    <div class="container-narrow">
      <span class="eyebrow">About</span>
      <h1>Making water research accessible to everyone, every day.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        SpeakForWater turns peer-reviewed water research into a 10-minute morning
        listen — so that scientists, policymakers, and curious citizens can stay
        current with the field without the friction of paywalls, jargon, or time.
      </p>

      <section class="block">
        <h2>Why water</h2>
        <p>
          Water defines whether civilizations thrive or fall. Two billion people
          lack safely managed drinking water. Aquifers are emptying faster than
          they refill. Rivers that once never reached the sea now run dry every
          year. The science addressing these crises is published every day —
          but most of it stays locked in journals that few read and fewer share.
        </p>
        <p>
          SpeakForWater exists to close that gap. Every weekday, a new paper
          becomes a podcast. The goal is not to replace the paper — it's to
          make sure more people actually engage with the research.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="block" id="methodology">
        <h2>Our methodology</h2>
        <p>
          Each morning, an automated pipeline scans <a href="https://openalex.org">OpenAlex</a>,
          arXiv, and a curated list of water journals for new open-access papers.
          A scoring agent ranks them by novelty, relevance, and accessibility.
          The top paper of the day is fed to <a href="https://notebooklm.google.com">Google's NotebookLM</a>,
          which generates a natural conversation between two AI hosts. The
          episode is reviewed, stitched with intro/outro music, and published
          here and on every major podcast platform.
        </p>
        <p>
          The full system is open source —
          <a href="https://github.com/Ehsankahrizi/speakforwater" rel="noopener">
            see the code on GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="block" id="ai">
        <h2>AI & ethics</h2>
        <p>
          Every episode of SpeakForWater is generated by AI. We are explicit
          about this for three reasons:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Transparency.</strong> Listeners deserve to know what they're
            hearing. Every episode page links to the original paper so you can
            verify what the AI hosts say.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Accuracy.</strong> AI-generated audio can hallucinate.
            We include a quality-check step that compares the transcript against
            the source paper before publishing — but mistakes still happen.
            If you spot one, <a href="mailto:hello@speakforwater.com">tell us</a>.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Credit.</strong> The science is the work of the researchers,
            not the AI. Every episode prominently links the paper, journal, and
            authors. We encourage you to read the original.
          </li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="block">
        <h2>About the maker</h2>
        <p>
          SpeakForWater is a project by <strong>Ehsan Kahrizi</strong> — a water
          resources researcher who believes hydrology should be in everyone's
          ears, not just on everyone's desks. The project is open source under
          the MIT license, and listening will always be free.
        </p>
        <p class="contact-row">
          <a href="mailto:hello@speakforwater.com" class="btn">Get in touch</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/Ehsankahrizi/speakforwater" class="btn" rel="noopener">View on GitHub</a>
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: 80px 0 96px;
  }

  .lede {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--c-ink-soft);
    margin: 18px 0 56px;
  }

  .block {
    margin-bottom: 48px;
  }

  .block h2 {
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    padding-bottom: 12px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--c-border);
  }

  .block p {
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: var(--c-ink-soft);
    margin-bottom: 1em;
  }

  .block ul {
    padding-left: 0;
    list-style: none;
  }

  .block li {
    font-size: 1.02rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--c-ink-soft);
    padding-left: 24px;
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 1em;
  }

  .block li::before {
    content: "—";
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
    color: var(--c-brand);
  }

  .contact-row {
    display: flex;
    gap: 12px;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    margin-top: 24px;
  }
</style>
